ANKARA, Turkey, January 12, 2022/APO Group/ -- 
                                                        
                            We are saddened to receive the news that at least 8 people lost their lives and many were injured in a bomb blast which took place today (12 January) at Waberi quarter in Mogadishu, Somalia.
                                We strongly condemn this heinous terrorist attack and extend our condolences to the brotherly people and Government of Somalia
                            



We strongly condemn this heinous terrorist attack and extend our condolences to the brotherly people and Government of Somalia. We wish Allah’s mercy upon those who lost their lives and a speedy recovery to the injured.

Türkiye will continue to stand by Somalia in its fight against terrorism.